{
  "stem": "2718.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But [? before ?] night, he-- he came home to sleep and then went back again next morning.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And as they marched through the village, and everybody was quite happy about it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And that was-- that was at that-- then, again, of course, when they turned-- the tide has turned, and the times have changed.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And the Hungarians have joined-- have joined the Germans in the war.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Because up to 19-- up to 1942, up to 1942, the-- the Hungarians were neutral.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Hungary was not-- not an active member of the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They were-- they were neutral, on the side of the Germans.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "On the 21st of June, 1942, Hungary entered the war and-- on the side of the Germans, and declared war on Russia.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "So from then on, things happened very quickly.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "From then on, the people were sent to the Russian front.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And the same time the army went to the Russian front, so the Jewish contingence also sent out, unfortunately, not in the-- not in the same comfortable way as the regular soldiers, but the same way as we were-- we were transported to Auschwitz in-- in cattle wagons-- in cattle cars.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And most of them didn't come back.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Because not only did they use them as digging trenches, but they also used them as-- as protecting themselves from the Russians.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "Because they thought if the Russians will see that the Jewish brigade, with the yellow arm bands, is-- is present somewhere, they will think twice before they shoot.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But the Russians couldn't care less about who they shot.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "They had a job to do.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "They were defending themselves.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And-- and it made no difference.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "So, unfortunately, from then on in was-- that is the time when we really got the message that something serious is happening.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
